>>selenium.webdriver → Module that controls browsers programmatically.

>>Chrome → Class used to launch and control the Chrome browser.

>>ChromeOptions → Class used to configure how Chrome should start.

>>Creating a ChromeOptions Object using
opt = ChromeOptions()
You use this object to:

--disable notifications

--run headless mode

--set user agents

--keep browser open after execution

--add extensions

>>detach holds the browser open --> detaches the browser session from the script.

>> driver = Chrome(options=opt) --> Launches browser obj with options
>> use driver now to control browser

>>driver.get("https://google.com") -->get a webpage
--> return type for get is none

>>driver.maximize_window() -->maximizes, return type is none
>>driver.minimize_window() -->minimizes, return type is none 
>>driver.fullscreen_window() -->no task or title bar, return type none


--SOME PROPERTIES--
>>title = driver.title //fetches title

>>print(driver.current_url) -->fetches curr current_url

>>print(driver.page_source) -->fetches html src

>>driver.name -->fetches driver name such as Chrome


--QUIT/CLOS/BACK/FORWARD/REFRESH--
>>driver.quit() -->closes all tabs

>>driver.close() -->closes one tab

>>driver.back() -->prev page

>>driver.forward() -->next page

>>driver.refresh()
